cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

The paper deals with the application of deep convolutional neural networks for semantic segmentation of medical images, specifically endoscopic images of the larynx. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning methods and network ensembling, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of data augmentation and patient-specific fine-tuning could also place it in cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), respectively.
